## Applying ARM Template

After exporting an ARM template, you can apply it to deploy resources in Azure using the following steps:

a. Azure Portal:

```
In the Azure Portal, search for "Deploy a custom template"6.
Select "Build your own template in the editor" or "Load a file" to upload your main template file2.
Fill in the required parameters or load your parameters file2.
Select the target resource group and review the deployment settings.
Click "Review + Create" and then "Create" to start the deployment2.
```

b. Azure PowerShell:

```
powershell
$templateFile = "path/to/your/azuredeploy.json"
$parameterFile = "path/to/your/azuredeploy.parameters.json"
New-AzResourceGroupDeployment `
  -Name YourDeploymentName `
  -ResourceGroupName YourResourceGroup `
  -TemplateFile $templateFile `
  -TemplateParameterFile $parameterFile
```

c. Azure CLI:

```
bash
az deployment group create \
  --name YourDeploymentName \
  --resource-group YourResourceGroup \
  --template-file path/to/your/azuredeploy.json \
  --parameters @path/to/your/azuredeploy.parameters.json
```
